subSubSection.paragraph:
Clerodendrum kamhyoae

has been collected in full flower from May to July, but observations at “Macolline” indicate that flowering typically starts in April and can continue sporadically until October (Kam Hyo Zschocke & Moscovitch, pers. comm.), and where flowering has been recorded at the site every year since its discovery. It has been collected in mature fruit in October (“Macolline”, 
Phillipson 6509
) and in December (Montagne d’Ambre, 
Ramandimbimanana 177
).
